# Layout & Spacing

## App shell: 16:9 product frame
The **entire** shell (sidebar + header + content) is drawn inside the **largest 16:9 rectangle** that fits the viewport: `.app-product-letterbox` centers it; `.app-product-frame` uses `width: min(100vw, 100vh×16/9)` and `height: min(100vh, 100vw×9/16)`. Non-16:9 viewports show **letterboxing** (gray bars). **Scrolling:** sidebar nav uses `overflow-y-auto` on its inner stack; **main** uses `flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-y-auto` on `.shell-main-canvas` so route content scrolls inside the main column. Routed content may also use a **max width 1440px** centered column via `.shell-main-canvas`.

## Page Container
- Padding: `px-[32px] pt-[12px] pb-[32px]`
- Background: `bg-[#ffffff]` (`bg-white`)
- Min height: `min-h-full`
- Section gap: `gap-4 md:gap-6`

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 md:gap-6 bg-white min-h-full px-[32px] pt-[12px] pb-[32px]">
```

## Edge-to-Edge Separators
Full-width lines that span outside the page padding:
```tsx
<div className="w-[calc(100%+64px)] h-[1px] bg-[#e0e0e0] mx-[-32px]" />
```

## Border Radius
| Element | Radius | Tailwind |
|---|---|---|
| Button | 8px | `rounded-[8px]` |
| Default | 8px | `rounded-lg` |
| Card | 12px | `rounded-[12px]` |
| Dashboard cards | 20px | `rounded-[20px]` |
| TextField | 4px | `rounded-[4px]` |
| Dropdown menu | 8px | `rounded-lg` |
| Full-round (avatar, pill) | 50% | `rounded-full` |

## Shadows & Elevation
- Small: `shadow-elevation-sm` → `0 8px 16px rgba(16,16,16,0.07)` — use sparingly for cards, dropdowns
- Drawer: `shadow-[-4px_0_24px_rgba(0,0,0,0.08)]`

## Component Internal Padding
- Cards: `p-5` (20px)
- Table cells: `px-6 py-4` (rows), `px-6 py-3` (headers)
- Modals/Popups: `px-8`
- Drawers: `px-8`

## Spacing Patterns
- Section gaps: `gap-4 md:gap-6`
- Card grid gaps: `gap-4` or `gap-6`
- Summary card strip: `gap-1` (4px) between cards + operator symbols
- Filter row gaps: `gap-5` (20px desktop), `gap-[15px]` (mobile)

## Scrollbar Styling
```
[&::-webkit-scrollbar]:w-2
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-track]:bg-transparent
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb]:bg-gray-300
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb]:rounded-full
[&::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb]:hover:bg-gray-400
```

## Interaction Patterns

### Hover States
- Cards: opacity change (60% → 100%) or background color change
- Buttons: background color lightening/darkening
- Links: underline appearance
- Dropdowns/rows: `hover:bg-[#f5f9fe]`

### Transitions
- Colors: `transition-colors`
- Shadows: `transition-shadow`
- Icon rotations: `transition-transform`
- Duration: default Tailwind timing (150–200ms)

### Click Outside Detection
```tsx
const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
useEffect(() => {
  const handler = (e: MouseEvent) => {
    if (ref.current && !ref.current.contains(e.target as Node)) setOpen(false);
  };
  document.addEventListener("mousedown", handler);
  return () => document.removeEventListener("mousedown", handler);
}, []);
```

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- Grid: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`
- Flex direction: `flex-col sm:flex-row`
- Spacing: `gap-4 md:gap-6`
- Padding: `p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8`

## Date & Time Formatting
- Date: "Today, 24 Jan" / "Yesterday, 23 Jan"
- Time: "7:30 AM, 23 Sep" / "8:00 AM Everyday"
- Use relative dates when appropriate

## Module & page layouts

Full-route / module specs (page shells, flows, multi-step layouts) live under this folder — not under `components/`:

| Rule file | Module |
|---|---|
| `layout/connect-plus.mdc` | Connect Plus activation |
| `layout/payment-pages.mdc` | Payment Pages (SwiftPay Builder) |
| `layout/payment-settings.mdc` | Settings → Payment settings |

Use `components/` rules for reusable UI pieces (buttons, cards, drawers); use `layout/*.mdc` for how entire pages or modules are structured.

## Common Mistakes
- DO NOT use arbitrary hex without design system reference
- DO NOT hardcode spacing values — use Tailwind spacing scale
- DO NOT forget transitions on interactive elements
- DO use CSS variables from theme.css
- DO provide hover states for all interactive elements
- DO ensure mobile responsiveness
